Package general

This package includes all the classes that are general to this kind of project, a simulation using events in an event container

The classes from this package are general to simulations and may be used in various contexts, like a simulation of a toll or a simulation of individuals moving around a map.

Author:
Group 6 - 81588, 81607 and 81669 Course of Object Oriented Programming
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    EventI
    Provides a method (guidelines) to be implemented in order to simulate events that are handled by the PECI implementations.
    INumberGenerator
    Provides a method to get a double from a random or deterministic number generator.
    PECI<E extends EventI>
    A container that provides operations made to a collection (it can be any kind of collection) of event classes that implement the interface EventI.
    SimulationI
    A simulator that provides methods to simulate events, with methods to simulate and initialize the simulation.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Event
    This class provides an initial implementation of the EventI interface to minimize the effort required to implement it in the case where the event is driven by its time.
    PEC
    This class provides an implementation of the PECI interface.
    SimulationA
    This class provides an abstract implementation of the SimulationI interface to minimize the effort required to implement it.
    SimulationCommands
    SimulationCommands contains the generators of numbers that implement the interface INumberGenerator necessary to run a simulation.
    TimeEventComparator
    TimeEventComparator implements Comparator of type Event and compares events of type Event according to their time, in ascendant order.
    Utils
    Class with static methods in order to facilitate the generation of random numbers.
